==In popular culture==
===Influence on the ''Elder Scrolls'' series===
The concept of kalpas was an inspiration for the kalpas of the universe of the ''[[The Elder Scrolls|Elder Scrolls]]'' series of [[Action role-playing game|action role-playing]] [[open world]] [[fantasy]] video games. In ''The Elder Scrolls'', kalpas represent each life cycle of the mortal realm of Mundus.<ref name="Paarthy">Paarthurnax's dialogue in ''[[The Elder Scrolls V: Skyrim]]''</ref>

===''City at the End of Time'' ===
In ''[[City at the End of Time]]'', a science fiction novel by [[Greg Bear]], Kalpa is a fortress city built on Earth by descendants of humans in the last period of the Universe to protect themselves from the Chaos that is devouring it.

