'''Mankari''' (Mānkari or Maankari) is a hereditary title used by [[Maratha]] [[Nobility|nobles]] who held land grants, and cash allowances.<ref name="google2">{{cite book|title=The Central India State Gazetteer Series|author1=Central India|author2=Luard, C.E.|date=1908|issue=v. 5, pt. 1|publisher=Thacker, Spink|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=1_4bAQAAIAAJ|accessdate=2015-07-12}}</ref> They held an official position at the [[Durbar (court)|Darbar]] ([[court]]) and were entitled to certain ceremonial honours and presents rendered at courts, councils, weddings, festivals, village assemblies, etc. They were worthy of distinction and the honour bestowed upon them was the result of the military, bureaucratic or fiscal importance of them or their distinguished ancestors.<ref name="google">{{cite book|title=Way of Life: King, Householder, Renouncer : Essays in Honour of Louis Dumont|author=Madan, T.N.|date=1988|publisher=Motilal Banarsidass|isbn=9788120805279|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=1_qMH9PY9fQC&pg=PA129|page=129|accessdate=2015-07-04}}</ref><ref>https://books.google.co.in/books?ei=OzGcVZGQA8XF0gTw8qSwDQ&id=xdIBAAAAMAAJ&dq=Mankar+being+primarily+a+title+applied+to+Maratha+noblemen%2C+who+held+an+official+position+at+court&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=Mankari+being+primarily+a+title+applied+to+Maratha+noblemen%2C+who+held+an+official+position+at+court</ref>
The term was widely used by [[Maratha]] [[nobility]], who held important positions in various [[List of Maratha dynasties and states|princely states]] of the [[Maratha Empire]].<ref name="google3">{{cite book|title=Caste, Conflict and Ideology: Mahatma Jotirao Phule and Low Caste Protest in Nineteenth-Century Western India|author=O'Hanlon, R.|date=2002|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=9780521523080|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=5kMrsTj1NeYC&pg=PA45|page=45|accessdate=2015-07-12}}</ref><ref>https://books.google.co.in/books?ei=azicVaz7L8Gw0ATJ4raoDw&id=THR5AAAAIAAJ&dq=The+person+entitled+%28from+office%2C+merit%29+to+certain+honours+and+presents+rendered+at+courts%2C+weddings%2C+councils+and+village-assemblies&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=mankari</ref>
